README.md

Awesome

   A collection of awesome Ruby Gems for Rails development.

   The goal is to help every Rails developer to build an awesome Rails
   product/service.
     * Rails Gem List
          + User
          + Active Record
          + Plugins
          + API
          + Email
          + File Uploading
          + Searching
          + Scheduled/Recurrence Jobs
          + View Helper
          + Environment Variables
          + Admin Panel
          + Logging
          + Debug
          + Coding Style
          + Testing
          + Production
          + Error Logging
          + Database

User

Authentication

     * [https://github.com/plataformatec/devise/]Devise - Devise is a
       flexible authentication solution for Rails based on Warden.
     * [https://github.com/nsarno/knock]Knock - Seamless JWT
       authentication for Rails API.
     * [https://github.com/thoughtbot/clearance]Clearance - Rails
       authentication with email & password.
     * [https://github.com/lynndylanhurley/devise_token_auth]Devise token
       auth - Token based authentication for Rails JSON APIs.
     * [https://github.com/Sorcery/sorcery]Sorcery - Magical
       Authentication for Rails. Supports ActiveRecord, DataMapper,
       Mongoid and MongoMapper.

Authorization

     * [https://github.com/elabs/pundit]Pundit - Pundit provides a set of
       helpers which guide you in leveraging regular Ruby classes and
       object oriented design patterns to build a simple, robust and
       scaleable authorization system.
     * [https://github.com/CanCanCommunity/cancancan]cancancan -
       Continuation of CanCan, the authorization Gem for Ruby on
       Rails.CanCan is an authorization library for Ruby on Rails which
       restricts what resources a given user is allowed to access. All
       permissions are defined in a single location (the Ability class)
       and not duplicated across controllers, views, and database queries.
     * [https://github.com/RolifyCommunity/rolify]rolify - Role management
       library with resource scoping.
     * [https://github.com/be9/acl9/]acl9 - Acl9 is a role-based
       authorization system that provides a concise DSL for securing your
       Rails application.

Omniauth

     * [https://github.com/mkdynamic/omniauth-facebook]omniauth-facebook
     * [https://github.com/zquestz/omniauth-google-oauth2]omniauth-google-
       oauth2
     * [https://github.com/beenhero/omniauth-weibo-oauth2]omniauth-weibo-o
       auth2
     * [https://github.com/arunagw/omniauth-twitter]omniauth-twitter
     * [https://github.com/intridea/omniauth-github]omniauth-github
     * [https://github.com/decioferreira/omniauth-linkedin-oauth2]omniauth
       -linkedin-oauth2

Active Record

     * [https://github.com/brainspec/enumerize]Enumerize - Enumerated
       attributes with I18n and ActiveRecord/Mongoid support. It can be
       integrated with Simple Form.
     * [https://github.com/magnusvk/counter_culture]counter_culture -
       Turbo-charged counter caches for your Rails app. Huge improvements
       over the Rails standard counter caches.
     * [https://github.com/cedric/custom_counter_cache]custom_counter_cach
       e - A simple approach to creating a custom counter cache that can
       be used across multiple models.
     * [https://github.com/djreimer/sequenced]Sequenced - Sequenced is a
       simple gem that generates scoped sequential IDs for ActiveRecord
       models.
     * [https://github.com/norman/friendly_id]FriendlyId - FriendlyId is
       the "Swiss Army bulldozer" of slugging and permalink plugins for
       ActiveRecord. It allows you to create pretty URL's and work with
       human-friendly strings as if they were numeric ids for ActiveRecord
       models.
     * [https://github.com/aasm/aasm]AASM - State machines for Ruby
       classes (plain Ruby, Rails Active Record, Mongoid).
     * [https://github.com/airblade/paper_trail]PaperTrail - PaperTrail
       lets you track changes to your models' data. It's good for auditing
       or versioning.
     * [https://github.com/rubysherpas/paranoia]paranoia - ActiveRecord
       plugin allowing you to hide and restore records without actually
       deleting them.
     * [https://github.com/kaize/validates]Validates - Validates provides
       collection of useful custom validators for Rails applications,
       including:
          + EmailValidator
          + UrlValidator
          + SlugValidator
          + MoneyValidator
          + IpValidator
          + AssociationLengthValidator
          + AbsolutePathValidator
          + UriComponentValidator
          + ColorValidator
          + EanValidator (EAN-8 & EAN-13)
     * [https://github.com/globalize/globalize]globalize - Rails I18n
       de-facto standard library for ActiveRecord model/data translation.
     * [https://github.com/moiristo/deep_cloneable]deep_cloneable - This
       gem gives every ActiveRecord::Base object the possibility to do a
       deep clone that includes user specified associations.
     * [https://github.com/Timrael/social_shares]social_shares - Check how
       many times url was shared in social networks.
     * [https://github.com/chaps-io/public_activity]public_activity - Easy
       activity tracking for models - similar to Github's Public Activity.
     * [https://github.com/salsify/goldiloader]goldiloader - Automatic
       ActiveRecord eager loading to reduce the number of database queries
       run by your application.
     * Tagging
          + [https://github.com/mbleigh/acts-as-taggable-on]ActsAsTaggable
            On - A tagging plugin for Rails applications that allows for
            custom tagging along dynamic contexts.
          + [https://github.com/mceachen/closure_tree]closure_tree -
            Easily and efficiently make your ActiveRecord models support
            hierarchies.
     * [https://github.com/rails-engine/action-store]ActionStore - Store
       different kind of actions (Like, Follow, Star, Block ...) in one
       table via ActiveRecord Polymorphic Association.

Plugins

     * [https://github.com/zdavatz/spreadsheet]Spreadsheet - Library is
       designed to read and write Spreadsheet Documents.
     * [https://github.com/ankane/chartkick]Chartkick - Chartkick helps
       your to create beautiful Javascript charts with one line of Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/amatsuda/kaminari]kaminari - A Scope & Engine
       based, clean, powerful, customizable and sophisticated paginator
       for Rails 3 and 4.
     * [https://github.com/galetahub/ckeditor]CKEditor - CKEditor is a
       WYSIWYG text editor designed to simplify web content creation. It
       brings common word processing features directly to your web pages.
       Enhance your website experience with our community maintained
       editor. [http://ckeditor.com/]ckeditor.com
     * [https://github.com/jch/html-pipeline]HTML::Pipeline - GitHub HTML
       processing filters and utilities. This module includes a small
       framework for defining DOM based content filters and applying them
       to user provided content.
     * [https://github.com/stevenosloan/slack-notifier]Slack Notifier is a
       simple wrapper to send notifications to [https://slack.com/]Slack
       webhooks.
     * [https://github.com/voormedia/rails-erd]Rails ERD - Generate
       Entity-Relationship Diagrams for Rails applications.
     * [https://github.com/thoughtbot/parity]Parity - Shell commands for
       development, staging, and production parity for Heroku apps.
     * [https://github.com/mattbrictson/airbrussh]Airbrussh - Airbrussh
       pretties up your SSHKit and Capistrano output

API

     * [https://github.com/ruby-grape/grape]Grape - Microframework to
       create REST-ful APIs in Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/rails-api/active_model_serializers]ActiveModel:
       :Serializers - Serializer brings convention over configuration to
       your JSON generation.
     * [https://github.com/rails/jbuilder]Jbuilder - Jbuilder gives you a
       simple DSL for declaring JSON structures that beats massaging giant
       hash structures. This is particularly helpful when the generation
       process is fraught with conditionals and loops.
     * [https://github.com/rest-client/rest-client]rest-client - Simple
       HTTP and REST client for Ruby, inspired by microframework syntax
       for specifying actions.
     * [https://github.com/plataformatec/has_scope]has_scope - Map
       incoming controller parameters to named scopes in your resources.
     * Documentation
          + [https://github.com/ruby-grape/grape-swagger]Grape Swagger -
            Autogenerate documentation on Grape API.
          + [https://github.com/swagger-api/swagger-ui]Grape Swagger UI -
            Display documentation that is generated using Grape Swagger.
          + [https://apiary.io/]apiary - Work together to quickly design,
            prototype, document and test APIs.
          + [https://apiblueprint.org/]apiblueprint - API Documentation
            with powerful tooling.

Email

     * [https://github.com/ryanb/letter_opener]letter_opener - Preview
       mail in the browser instead of sending.

File Uploading

     * [https://github.com/carrierwaveuploader/carrierwave]Carrierwave -
       Carrierwave is a classier solution for file uploads for Rails,
       Sinatra and other Ruby web frameworks.
          + [https://github.com/lardawge/carrierwave_backgrounder]carrierw
            ave_backgrounder - Offload CarrierWave's image processing and
            storage to a background process using Delayed Job, Resque,
            Sidekiq, Qu, Queue Classic or Girl Friday.
          + [https://github.com/kirtithorat/carrierwave-crop/]CarrierWave
            Crop - Carrierwave extension to crop uploaded images using
            Jcrop plugin with preview.
          + [https://github.com/jtescher/carrierwave-imageoptimizer]Carrie
            rWave ImageOptimizer - This gem allows you to simply optimize
            CarrierWave images via jpegoptim or optipng using the
            image_optimizer gem.
     * [https://github.com/JangoSteve/remotipart]remotipart - Rails jQuery
       file uploads via standard Rails "remote: true" forms.
     * [https://github.com/minimagick/minimagick]MiniMagick - MiniMagick
       is a ruby wrapper for ImageMagick or GraphicsMagick command line.
     * [https://github.com/fog/fog]fog - Fog is the Ruby cloud services
       library, top to bottom.
     * [https://github.com/refile/refile]refile - Refile is a modern file
       upload library for Ruby applications. It is simple, yet powerful.
     * [https://github.com/thoughtbot/paperclip]Paperclip - Easy file
       attachment management for ActiveRecord.
     * [http://markevans.github.io/dragonfly]Dragonfly - Dragonfly is for
       on-the-fly file processing - suitable for images or other
       attachments
     * [https://github.com/janko-m/shrine]shrine -File Attachment toolkit
       for Ruby applications

Searching

     * [https://github.com/activerecord-hackery/ransack]ransack - Ransack
       enables the creation of both simple and advanced search forms for
       your Ruby on Rails application.
     * [https://github.com/elastic/elasticsearch-rails]elasticsearch-rails
       - Elasticsearch integrations for ActiveModel/Record and Ruby on
       Rails.
     * [https://github.com/toptal/chewy]Chewy - High-level Elasticsearch
       Ruby framework based on the official elasticsearch-ruby client.
     * [https://github.com/Casecommons/pg_search]pg_search - pg_search
       builds ActiveRecord named scopes that take advantage of
       PostgreSQL's full text search
     * [https://github.com/sunspot/sunspot]sunspot - Sunspot is a Ruby
       library for expressive, powerful interaction with the Solr search
       engine. Sunspot is built on top of the RSolr library, which
       provides a low-level interface for Solr interaction; Sunspot
       provides a simple, intuitive, expressive DSL backed by powerful
       features for indexing objects and searching for them.
     * [https://github.com/ankane/searchkick]searchkick - Intelligent
       search made easy with Rails and Elasticsearch.

Scheduled/Recurrence Jobs

     * [https://github.com/javan/whenever]Whenever - Whenever is a Ruby
       gem that provides a clear syntax for writing and deploying cron
       jobs.
     * [https://github.com/resque/resque]Resque - Redis-backed Ruby
       library for creating background jobs, placing them on multiple
       queues, and processing them later.
     * [https://github.com/jmettraux/rufus-scheduler]Rufus-Scheduler -
       Rufus-scheduler is a Ruby gem for scheduling pieces of code (jobs).
       It understands running a job AT a certain time, IN a certain time,
       EVERY x time or simply via a CRON statement.
     * [https://github.com/collectiveidea/delayed_job]Delayed Job -
       Database based asynchronous priority queue system.
     * [https://github.com/mperham/sidekiq]Sidekiq - Simple, efficient
       background processing for Ruby.
          + [https://github.com/tobiassvn/sidetiq]sidetiq - Recurring jobs
            for sidekiq.
          + [https://github.com/ondrejbartas/sidekiq-cron]sidekiq-cron -
            Scheduler / Cron for Sidekiq jobs
          + [https://github.com/Moove-it/sidekiq-scheduler]sidekiq-schedul
            er - Lightweight job scheduler extension for Sidekiq
     * [https://github.com/brandonhilkert/sucker_punch]Sucker Punch -
       Sucker punch is a single-process Ruby asynchronous processing
       library.

View Helper

     * [https://github.com/justinfrench/formtastic]formtastic - Formtastic
       is a Rails FormBuilder DSL (with some other goodies) to make it far
       easier to create beautiful, semantically rich, syntactically
       awesome, readily stylable and wonderfully accessible HTML forms in
       your Rails applications
     * [https://github.com/plataformatec/simple_form]Simple Form - Simple
       form aims to be as flexible as possible while helping you with
       powerful components to create your forms. The basic goal of Simple
       Form is to not touch your way of defining the layout, letting you
       find the better design for your eyes.
     * [https://github.com/ryanb/nested_form]Nested Form - This is a Rails
       gem for conveniently manage multiple nested models in a single
       form. It does so in an unobtrusive way through jQuery or Prototype.
       It can also be integrated with Simple Form.
     * [https://github.com/kpumuk/meta-tags]meta-tags - Search Engine
       Optimization (SEO) plugin for Ruby on Rails applications.
     * [https://github.com/comfy/active_link_to]active_link_to -
       active_link_to adds css 'active' class to your links.
     * [https://github.com/apotonick/cells]cells - Cells allow you to
       encapsulate parts of your UI into components into view models. View
       models, or cells, are simple ruby classes that can render
       templates.
     * [https://github.com/onomojo/i18n_country_select]i18n Country Code
       Select - I18n Country Code Select Form Helper for Rails 3 & 4.
     * [https://github.com/cllns/subdivision_select]Subdivision Select - A
       Rails plugin to populate a state/province select box from
       country_select.
     * [https://github.com/nathanvda/cocoon]cocoon - Dynamic nested forms
       using jQuery made easy

Environment Variables

     * [https://github.com/railsconfig/config]Config - Multi-environment
       YAML style configurations that helps easily manage environment
       specific settings in an easy and usable manner.
     * [https://github.com/laserlemon/figaro]Figaro - Figaro is very
       simple, Heroku-friendly Rails app configuration using ENV and a
       single YAML file.
     * [https://github.com/bkeepers/dotenv]dotenv - Dotenv is a gem that
       allows you to set your environment variables in .env file, and it
       will load it in to ENV.
     * [https://github.com/mikamai/opsworks-dotenv]opsworks-dotenv -
       Opsworks-dotenv let you configure the environment for you Rails
       application using OpsWorks, Chef and Dotenv.

Admin Panel

     * [http://activeadmin.info/]ActiveAdmin - ActiveAdmin is a
       administration framework for Ruby on Rails applications.
          + [https://github.com/rstgroup/active_skin]active_skin: Flat
            skin for active admin.
     * [https://github.com/sferik/rails_admin]RailsAdmin - RailsAdmin is a
       Rails engine that provides an easy-to-use interface for managing
       your data.
     * [https://github.com/typus/typus]Typus - Typus is a control panel
       for Ruby on Rails applications to allow trusted users edit
       structured content.
     * [https://github.com/thoughtbot/administrate]administrate - A Rails
       engine that helps you put together a super-flexible admin
       dashboard.
     * [https://github.com/TrestleAdmin/trestle]Trestle - A modern,
       responsive admin framework for Ruby on Rails

Logging

     * [https://github.com/charlotte-ruby/impressionist]Impressionist -
       Impressionist can log page impressions (technically action
       impressions), but it is not limited to that. You can log
       impressions multiple times per request. And you can also attach it
       to a model. The goal of this project is to provide customizable
       stats that are immediately accessible in your application as
       opposed to using Google Analytics and pulling data using their API.
     * [https://github.com/ankane/ahoy]Ahoy - Ahoy provides a solid
       foundation to track visits and events in Ruby, JavaScript, and
       native apps.
     * [https://github.com/roidrage/lograge]Lograge - An attempt to tame
       Rails' default policy to log everything.

Debug

     * [https://github.com/deivid-rodriguez/byebug]byebug - Byebug is a
       simple to use, feature rich debugger for Ruby 2. It uses the new
       TracePoint API for execution control and the new Debug Inspector
       API for call stack navigation, so it doesn't depend on internal
       core sources.
          + [https://github.com/deivid-rodriguez/pry-byebug]pry-byebug -
            Pry navigation commands via byebug.
     * [https://github.com/rweng/pry-rails]pry-rails - Avoid repeating
       yourself, use pry-rails instead of copying the initializer to every
       rails project. This is a small gem which causes rails console to
       open pry. It therefore depends on pry.
     * [https://github.com/awesome-print/awesome_print]awesome_print -
       Awesome Print is a Ruby library that pretty prints Ruby objects in
       full color exposing their internal structure with proper
       indentation.
     * [https://github.com/rails/web-console]web-console - Web Console is
       a debugging tool for your Ruby on Rails applications.
     * [https://github.com/rails/spring]spring - Spring is a Rails
       application preloader. It speeds up development by keeping your
       application running in the background so you don't need to boot it
       every time you run a test, rake task or migration.
     * [https://github.com/josevalim/rails-footnotes]rails-footnotes -
       Rails footnotes displays footnotes in your application for easy
       debugging, such as sessions, request parameters, cookies, filter
       chain, routes, queries, etc.
     * [https://github.com/jugyo/g]g - The Kernel.g that works like
       Kernel.p by using terminal-notifier or growl.
     * [https://github.com/julienXX/terminal-notifier]terminal-notifier -
       terminal-notifier is a command-line tool to send Mac OS X User
       Notifications, which are available in Mac OS X 10.8 and higher.
     * [https://github.com/ryanb/letter_opener]letter_opener - Preview
       email in the default browser instead of sending it. This means you
       do not need to set up email delivery in your development
       environment, and you no longer need to worry about accidentally
       sending a test email to someone else's address.
     * [https://github.com/charliesome/better_errors]Better Errors -
       Better errors replaces the standard Rails error page with a much
       better and more useful error page.
          + If you would like to use Better Errors' advanced features
            (REPL, local/instance variable inspection, pretty stack frame
            names), you need to add the
            [https://github.com/banister/binding_of_caller]binding_
            _of__caller.
     * [https://github.com/dejan/rails_panel]RailsPanel - RailsPanel is a
       Chrome extension for Rails development that will end your tailing
       of development.log.

Coding Style

     * [https://github.com/bbatsov/rubocop]RuboCop - Rubocop is a Ruby
       static code analyzer. Out of the box it will enforce many of the
       guidelines outlined in the community
       [https://github.com/bbatsov/ruby-style-guide]Ruby Style Guide.
     * [https://github.com/railsbp/rails_best_practices]Rails Best
       Practice - Rails best practice is a code metric tool to check the
       quality of rails codes.
     * [https://github.com/metricfu/metric_fu]Metric Fu - A fist full of
       code metrics
     * [https://github.com/mmozuras/pronto]Pronto - Quick automated code
       review of your changes

Testing

     * [https://github.com/rspec/rspec-rails]rspec-rails - Rspec-rails is
       a testing framework for Rails 3.x and 4.x.
     * [https://github.com/jnicklas/capybara]Capybara - Capybara helps you
       test web applications by simulating how a real user would interact
       with your app. And drivers:
          + [https://github.com/thoughtbot/capybara-webkit]capybara-webkit
            - Capybara-webkit is a capybara driver that uses Webkit via
            QtWebkit.
          + [https://github.com/vertis/selenium-webdriver]selenium-webdriv
            er - Selenium-webdriver provides ruby bindings for WebDriver.
          + [https://github.com/teampoltergeist/poltergeist]poltergeist -
            Poltergeist allows you to run your Capybara tests on a
            headless WebKit browser, provided by PhantomJS.
          + [https://github.com/cheezy/page-object]page-object -
            Page-object is a simple gem that assists in creating flexible
            page objects for testing browser based applications.
     * [https://github.com/thoughtbot/factory_bot]factory_bot -
       Factory_bot is a fixtures replacement with a straightforward
       definition syntax, support for multiple build strategies (saved
       instances, unsaved instances, attribute hashes, and stubbed
       objects), and support for multiple factories for the same class
       (user, admin_user, and so on), including factory inheritance.
     * [https://github.com/thoughtbot/factory_bot_rails]factory_bot_rails
       - Factory_bot_rails provides Rails integration for factory_bot.
     * [https://github.com/st0012/factory_factory_girl]factory_factory_gir
       l - FactoryFactoryGirl lets you generate factory files more
       efficiently with naming rules.
     * [https://github.com/DatabaseCleaner/database_cleaner]Database
       Cleaner - Database Cleaner is a set of strategies for cleaning your
       database in Ruby.Support ActiveRecord, DataMapper, Sequel,
       MongoMapper, Mongoid, CouchPotato, Ohm and Redis.
     * [https://github.com/thoughtbot/shoulda-matchers]shoulda-matchers -
       Shoulda-matchers provides serveral matchers for testing common
       Rails functionality.
     * [https://github.com/r7kamura/response_code_matchers]ResponseCodeMat
       chers - ResponseCodeMatchers provides rspec matchers to match http
       response code.
     * [https://github.com/colszowka/simplecov]SimpleCov - SimpleCov is a
       code coverage analysis tool for Ruby.
     * [https://github.com/travisjeffery/timecop]Timecop - A gem providing
       "time travel" and "time freezing" capabilities, making it dead
       simple to test time-dependent code.
     * [https://github.com/vcr/vcr]VCR - Record your test suite's HTTP
       interactions and replay them during future test runs for fast,
       deterministic, accurate tests.

Security

     * [https://github.com/presidentbeef/brakeman]brakeman - Brakeman is a
       static analysis tool which checks Ruby on Rails applications for
       security vulnerabilities.
     * [https://github.com/rubysec/bundler-audit]bundle-audit -
       bundler-audit is a patch-level verification tool for Bundler which
       checks for vulnerable versions of gems and insecure gem sources.
     * [https://github.com/twitter/secureheaders]Secure Headers - Secure
       Headers will automatically apply several headers that are related
       to security.

Production

     * [https://github.com/capistrano/capistrano]Capistrano - Remote
       multi-server automation tool.
     * [https://github.com/ankane/slowpoke]Slowpoke - Rack::Timeout is
       great. Slowpoke makes it better.
     * [https://github.com/kickstarter/rack-attack]Rack Attack - Rack
       middleware to blocking & throttling.
     * [https://github.com/plataformatec/responders]Responders - A set of
       Rails responders to dry up your application.
     * [https://github.com/ankane/production_rails]production_rails - Best
       practices for running Rails in production.
     * [https://github.com/mina-deploy/mina]Mina - fast deployer and
       server automation tool.

Error Logging

     * [https://github.com/rollbar/rollbar-gem]Rollbar - Exception
       tracking and logging from Ruby to Rollbar.
     * [https://github.com/airbrake/airbrake]Airbrake - Notifier gem for
       integrating apps with Airbrake
     * [https://github.com/errbit/errbit]Errbit - Open source notifier gem
       compliant with Airbrake.

Database

     * [https://github.com/igorkasyanchuk/rails_db]rails_db - Rails
       Database Viewer and SQL Query Runner

Asset Pipeline

     * [https://github.com/mavenlink/alaska]Alaska - ExecJS runtime with
       persistent connection to nodejs, speeds up your coffeescript
       compilation process during development and deployment.

